arent; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">build on strengths (don’t focus on your weaknesses</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Camp 3, “How can we all grow”</span></li>\r\n</ol></li>\r\n</ol></div>\r\n<div style=\"background-color: transparent;\"><br /><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">if you get all these: This is the summit</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"background-color: transparent;\"></div>\r\n<div style=\"background-color: transparent;\"></div>\r\n</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</span><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; line-height: normal; font-size: medium;\">\r\n<div style=\"background-color: transparent;\"><strong><span id=\"internal-source-marker_0.36586506152525544\" style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">4 Master Keys</span></strong><ol>\r\n<li style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><strong>Select for Talent </strong> (not equivalent to experience, race, university,fraternity, etc.)</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Define the Right Outcomes</span></strong><ol>\r\n<li style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">no need to micro manage if you go by results</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">easier to measure what is clearly defined</span></li>\r\n</ol></li>\r\n<li style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Focus on Strengths</span></strong><ol>\r\n<li style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Doesn’t work to change weaknesses in talent!</span></li>\r\n</ol></li>\r\n<li style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Find the Right Fit</span></strong><ol>\r\n<li style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Skills can be built. But don’t take people outside of their nature aptitudes</span></li>\r\n</ol></li>\r\n</ol></div>\r\n</span></p>','2011-08-09 20:46:03',0,''),(4,0,47,167,'2011-08-17 18:16:35','Port au Prince in December or January?','<p>After our amazing trip in July/August, we now know there is much work to do in Haiti. I know that others are planning on developing games; I\'m going to Port au Prince to reconnect with our contacts in Haiti (UMCOR, UMVIS, and OLPC people). I\'m either going at the end of the UNC Charlotte fall semester, or ideally over the January 12 Earthquake Remembrance (although that may be a chaotic time).</p>\r\n<p>If you want to see my (long-winded) thoughts on the experience in and around Cap Haitien, go to my blog at <a href=\"http://drgrossuncc.blogspot.com\">http://drgrossuncc.blogspot.com</a>.</p>','2011-08-17 18:50:56',0,''),(6,0,47,129,'2011-09-06 16:24:09','XO laptops','<p>Any word on the possibility of getting XO laptops?</p>\r\n<p>Barb Ericson</p>','2011-10-20 18:46:18',0,''),(96,0,81,185,'2013-02-02 17:36:43','UNC Charlotte Lab Visit','<p>We can put our plans, etc here. That way if we ever want to do this again, we have a list of contacts and ideas.</p>','2013-02-07 15:52:23',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":0}'),(97,0,66,45,'2013-02-04 17:34:04','Online Community bugs and feedback','<p>Rather than try and talk on the call today, I\'ll just start a discussion.</p>\r\n<p>Now that we are using the online community more, not surprisingly we are finding more bugs or functionality that just does not work as we thought it should. Reply to this discussion, or email me (my email address is at the bottom of every page) if you find a bug, have a question, or just think something isn\'t working like you want it to and we will fix things as quickly as we can. And tell your students to do the same.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks!</p>\r\n<p> </p>','2013-02-04 17:34:04',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":1}'),(8,0,42,42,'2011-09-19 14:45:24','Outreach and Recruitment Updates?!','<p>Now that the semester is off and running we\'d like to hear what you\'re doing for outreach and recruitment! Post your ideas, events and activities here to share!</p>\r\n<p>We also want to hear from you if you\'re having difficulty with your outreach efforts and will offer support where we can!</p>','2011-09-19 14:45:24',0,''),(9,0,46,42,'2011-09-19 14:47:01','What\'s Happening?','<p>How are all the fabulous Girl Geeks? What has been going on in the first month of the semester?! Send us updates and happenings from your groups and projects so far!</p>','2011-09-19 14:47:01',0,''),(11,0,45,42,'2011-09-19 14:52:06','Semester Ups and Downs?','<p>How is your semester going as a transfer student thus far? Are there  concerns or questions you have for us on how to be successful? Ideas for  making STARS even more inclusive? Share your thoughts with us so we can  make your learning experience as wonderful as possible!</p>','2011-09-19 14:52:06',0,''),(12,0,40,42,'2011-09-19 15:19:08','How are our Newbies?','<p>We are so delighted to have our new member schools this year in STARS and we want to hear from YOU! How is it going so far this semester? Are your students excited about their opportunities? How is recruitment going for new students? Are there concerns or struggles you are having? Let us know how we can help you and fully benefit from the great community you have become a part of!</p>','2011-10-01 11:02:43',0,''),(13,0,38,42,'2011-09-19 15:23:28','Past REU\'s and Future Ideas?','<p>How was your summer experiencing an REU? Let us know what fabulous and inventive projects you worked on so we can share them with other students and promote the great opportunities that REU\'s possess!</p>\r\n<p>Are you thinking of apply for an REU next year? Let us know if you have questions or are struggling with how to find the best fit for you!</p>','2011-09-26 22:27:19',0,''),(14,0,36,42,'2011-09-19 15:26:32','What\'s New?','<p>How is the mentoring going this semester? Are you finding new ways to challenge yourself and create opportunities within STARS? Share with us how your are mentoring or utilizing the program!</p>','2011-11-14 04:08:27',0,''),(15,0,47,75,'2011-09-21 03:19:08','Haitian Creole App and other Language Learning Tools','<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; color: #1f497d;\">A friend highly recommends the <a href=\"http://itunes.apple.com/us/app/byki-haitian-creole/id350651748?mt=8\" target=\"_blank\">Byki Haitian Creole</a> App. If you try it, let us know what you think.  If you know of any other Haitian Creole translation tools, post them here.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; color: #1f497d;\">Felesia</span></p>\r\n</p>','2012-02-06 03:03:00',0,''),(16,0,42,117,'2011-09-28 19:54:14','Have Marketing Material - STARS postcards and Dot.Diva brochures','<p>Just ping me at aschow@uncg.edu if you want some STARS postcards or Dot.Diva brochures....</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Cheers,</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>ASC</p>','2011-09-28 19:54:14',0,''),(17,0,6,139,'2011-09-29 17:47:21','FAMU SLC Committee Assignments - Fall 2011','<p>Students,</p>\r\n<p>Here are the committee assignments for Fall 2011 / Spring 2012:</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">EVALUATION COMMITTEE: </span></strong>Solange Artie, Chair;  Olivia Wilson, Co-Chair (Duties: work with STARS to evaluate SLC)</p>\r\n<p>- CLOSED (only chairs on this committee)</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>(FULL)  Community Service: </strong></span>Nathalie Cook, Chair  (Duties:  Community Service projects)</p>\r\n<p>Sharielle Johnson               Jessica Mann</p>\r\n<p>Bonita O\'Banion                 Alycia Gant</p>\r\n<p>Ashley Johnson                 Katrice St. Rose</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Education/Outreach: </strong></span>Angel Bobo, Chair; Jykia Johnson, Co-Chair  (Duties: working with kids in schools, recruitment projects, workshops)</p>\r\n<p>Shina Aofolaju                  Brittany Brown</p>\r\n<p>Olivia Wilson</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Professional Development: </strong></span>Lila Mandela, Chair (Duties:  work with Dr. Black to set up seminars, etc.)</p>\r\n<p>Sharielle Johnson</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Mentoring: </span></strong> Kai Dumont, Chair;  Sihle Wilson, Co-Chair  (Duties: work with Crystal and CISMO on Mentoring Activities)</p>\r\n<p>Dessirree Gray</p>\r\n<p>Crystal Williams (Honorary)</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Campus Activities: </strong></span> Jessica Mann, Chair  (Duties:  assist STARS in establishing a campus-wide presence through tables, SGA)</p>\r\n<p>Crystal Williams                 Nathalie Cook</p>\r\n<p>Aarmondas Walker</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Social Activities: </strong></span> Melanie Mitchell, Chair  (Duties:  help plan fun, social events for students in the SLC, fun trips, etc.)</p>\r\n<p>Olivia Wilson                    Tene\' Newman</p>\r\n<p>Brittany Brown</p>\r\n<p> </p>','2011-09-29 17:47:21',0,''),(18,0,40,118,'2011-09-29 20:13:07','Recruiting Resources','<p>Hello all!  I just uploaded some files to the \"New Members\" folder found under \"Sharing -> Resources\".  Melinda and Sandy created these files and had a good turnout at the first STARS information session at SSC on Monday evening.  We thought we would post the PPT presentation, Flyer and Invitation Letter for anyone else that might want to take a look!  Hope all is well!</p>','2011-10-28 13:18:43',0,''),(69,0,42,273,'2012-08-17 13:01:53','SPARCS outreach materials','<p>\r\n<div style=\"border-collapse: collapse; color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: normal;\">For those of you who came to the SPARCS workshop at the conference, here are the links we mentioned.</div>\r\n<div style=\"border-collapse: collapse; color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: normal;\">SPARCS resources include workshops on: GameMaker, Android AppInventor, CSUnplugged, WebDesign, Lego Mindstorms, Logic/Circuitry, Security & Encryption.</div>\r\n<div style=\"border-collapse: collapse; color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: normal;\"></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"border-collapse: collapse; color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: normal;\">SPARCS resources + lesson plans & 5 years of feedback data: <a href=\"https://sites.google.com/a/ncsu.edu/sparcs-resources/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: #1155cc;\">https://sites.google.com/a/ncsu.edu/sparcs-resources/<br /> </a></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"border-collapse: collapse; color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: normal;\">UNC Charlotte SPARCS page (resources used in weekly format + monthly format): <a href=\"http://unccslc.starsalliance.org/sparcs\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: #1155cc;\">http://unccslc.starsalliance.org/sparcs<br /> </a></span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"border-collapse: collapse; color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: normal;\">NCSU SPARCS page (resources used in monthly format): <a href=\"http://research.csc.ncsu.edu/stars/sparcs\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: #1155cc;\">http://research.csc.ncsu.edu/stars/sparcs<br /> </a></span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"border-collapse: collapse; color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: normal;\">School pages were made using Drupal (free + out of the box ready to use): <a href=\"http://drupal.org/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: #1155cc;\">http://drupal.org/</a></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</p>','2012-08-17 13:01:53',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":\"1\"}'),(23,0,28,332,'2011-10-01 11:09:00','Introduction','<p>Hello, I am Jessica and I am the current Vice President of the Digital Media Club at the Heathrow campus. I enjoy the Digital Media side of things as well as Programing. I am still learning programing but the different languages amaze me. I am always willing to help where I am able to. Can\'t wait for our program to kick off!</p>','2011-10-01 23:32:26',0,''),(24,0,56,151,'2011-10-08 03:37:53','New Robotics Team at UNCC','<p>I can say for sure that the UNC Charlotte\'s STARS robotics team is excited to join in with ARTSI on robotics outreach! We are planning to implement as many educational techniques that you guys can recommend :).</p>','2011-10-08 03:37:53',0,''),(25,0,6,139,'2011-10-09 19:14:35','Upcoming Event - Teen Summit (10/12, 6 -8p)','<hr />\r\n<p>Greetings.  STARS/AAWCS is hosting a Teen Summit for middle and high school students, on Wed. Oct. 12, 6 to 8p at Jake Gaither Community Center and Golf Course.  We need students to volunteer to help.  Click YES under the event on,this page if you can attemd.  Can be an activity.  Please respond by Mon. Oct. 10.  Jessica Herd is coordinating.</p>','2011-10-09 19:14:35',0,''),(26,0,6,139,'2011-10-12 17:15:38','UPDATED:  STARS / AAWCS Committee Assignments (as of 10/12/11)','<p>Students,</p>\r\n<p>Here are the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>UPDATED </strong></span>committee assignments for Fall 2011 / Spring 2012:</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">EVALUATION COMMITTEE: </span></strong>Solange Artie, Chair;  Olivia Wilson, Co-Chair (Duties: work with STARS to evaluate SLC)</p>\r\n<p>- CLOSED (only chairs on this committee)</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>(FULL)  Community Service: </strong></span>Nathalie Cook, Chair  (Duties:  Community Service projects)</p>\r\n<p>Sharielle Johnson               Jessica Mann             Vivian Williams</p>\r\n<p>Bonita O\'Banion                 Alycia Gant</p>\r\n<p>Ashley Johnson                 Katrice St. Rose</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Education/Outreach: </strong></span>Angel Bobo, Chair; Jykia Johnson, Co-Chair  (Duties: working with kids in schools, recruitment projects, workshops)</p>\r\n<p>Shina Aofolaju                  Brittany Brown</p>\r\n<p>Olivia Wilson                     Shina Aofolaju</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Professional Development: </strong></span>Lila Mandela, Chair (Duties:  work with Dr. Black to set up seminars, etc.)</p>\r\n<p>Sharielle Johnson             Maynard Yates</p>\r\n<p>Sihle Wilson                    Joshua Mack</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Mentoring: </span></strong> Kai Dumont, Chair;  Sihle Wilson, Co-Chair  (Duties: work with Crystal and CISMO on Mentoring Activities)</p>\r\n<p>Dessirree Gray</p>\r\n<p>Crystal Williams (Honorary)</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Campus Activities: </strong></span> Jessica Mann, Chair  (Duties:  assist STARS in establishing a campus-wide presence through tables, SGA)</p>\r\n<p>Crystal Williams                 Nathalie Cook</p>\r\n<p>Aarmondas Walker</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Social Activities: </strong></span> Melanie Mitchell, Chair  (Duties:  help plan fun, social events for students in the SLC, fun trips, etc.)</p>\r\n<p>Olivia Wilson                    Tene\' Newman</p>\r\n<p>Brittany Brown</p>','2011-10-12 17:15:38',0,''),(27,0,21,244,'2011-10-12 19:33:44','Tasks?','<p>Hello fellow members. I wish to discuss the following topics on certain goals im currently intrested in for us to accomplish. I really like the idea of going to some local highschools and show them how to either (A) Inform them on our CP major (B) Showcase what CP majors actually do. Anyone has anything to add please do so. Thanks.</p>','2011-11-03 16:45:20',0,''),(28,0,44,332,'2011-10-13 19:51:38','Stars Offical Logo','<p style=\"line-height: 15.6pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Tahoma&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; color: #333333; font-size: 9pt;\">Hello I was wondering if anyone knew where we would locate the EPS vector Logo For Stars Alliance along with the legal guidelines for like fliers. </span></p>','2011-10-17 06:13:55',0,''),(29,0,40,118,'2011-10-16 02:09:17','YouTube video requirements','<p>I\'ve been looking in the online community and on the STARS website and I haven\'t been able to find a list of requirements for our YouTube video - are there any defined requirements for this?  Thank you!</p>','2011-12-07 04:06:38',0,''),(30,0,40,149,'2011-10-18 17:22:41','Questions about STARS requirements','<p>Hi All:</p>\r\n<p>I am posting this discussion requesting input about the following items:<br />1.  How do you track student hours working on their activities?  Do all students need to track hours?<br />2.  How are you all managing funding?  Do you have a bank account for your group or do you have an acct. through your university/school?<br />3.  Mentoring.....please reply with examples and samples of mentoring activities and do they apply to only our STARS students or does it concern  others outside the group?  Does advising satisfy the mentoring aspect for STARS</p>\r\n<p>Thank you in advance for your input, as we were curious how others are handling the above items.<br />I look forward to hearing back from you!</p>','2011-10-28 13:07:21',0,''),(31,0,37,91,'2011-10-20 15:33:28','Presentation to potential partner schools','<p>Hey everyone!</p>\r\n<p>Wilberforce University is anticipating bringing CSDTs to our local community schools. Is there anyone who could recommend a sells pitch or what we can include in our presentation about STARS/ our project in order to get the schools interested in participating in our study?</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Thanks,</p>\r\n<p>Jonnel A. Ransom</p>\r\n<p>Wilberforce University</p>\r\n<p>Evaluation Assistant</p>','2011-10-20 15:33:28',0,''),(32,0,6,163,'2011-11-11 23:57:36','A chance to earn STARS Activity Points!!','<div class=\"clabel\">Event: Join AAWCS and the STARS Alliance for the viewing of CNN TV Special \" Black in America, Silicon Valley\"</div>\r\n<div class=\"clabel\">Location:</div>\r\n<div id=\"community-event-data-location\" class=\"cdata\">Cropper Hall Common Area at FAMU</div>\r\n<div class=\"cparam event-created\">\r\n<div class=\"cdata small\"><span>Time </span>Sunday, 13 November 2011 07:45 PM</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"cparam event-tickets\">\r\n<div class=\"clabel\">Event Details</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"event-desc\">\r\n<p><em><strong>****AAWCS and STARS Members, please come out and support the cause. This will be advertised to students in Gibbs and Cropper Hall as well as friends of friends. This will also count as activity points!! Due to limited funding, I am encouraging everyone to bring  a snack. If you are able to attend or would like to assist with this event, please email me at </strong><a href=\"mailto:jessicaherd@hotmail.com\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"color: #cc0033;\">jessicaherd@hotmail.com</span></span></strong></a><strong>. ****</strong></em></p>\r\n<p>Join African American Women in Computer Science and the STARS Alliance as we watch CNN\'s TV Special, \"Black in America Silicon Valley\"</p>\r\n<p>Purpose: Our goal is to increase the awareness of STEM majors and business options in technology.</p>\r\n<p>Background: Silicon Valley is the leader of innovation and development. Silicon Valley is home to many technological corporations like Google, Yahoo, Skype, BAE Systems, Adobe Systems, Cisco, Facebook and much more. However, currently less than one percent of all venture capital money went to digital start ups with African-American founders in 2010. This documentary will follow eight strangers as they help other entepreneurs secure funding to establish technology focused businesses despite racism, statistics and criticism.</p>\r\n<p>If you have questions contact Angel Bobo at               209-496-5292        209-496-5292 or Jessica Herd at               850-274-5649        850-274-5649 or by email <a href=\"mailto:jessicaherd@hotmail.com\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"color: #cc0033;\">jessicaherd@hotmail.com</span></span></a></p>\r\n</div>','2011-11-11 23:57:36',0,''),(33,0,10,350,'2011-11-15 17:59:15','Test discussion','<p>Matt,</p>\r\n<p>I\'m posting this so hopefully you can now see my account. Feel free to delete this upon verification.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p> </p>','2011-11-15 17:59:15',0,''),(34,0,23,318,'2011-11-16 21:06:24','AU STARS Fall Outreach','<p>Hi AuburnStars, Please share some of your highlight from this semester\'s outreach activities.</p>\r\n<p>Have a productive week and a great Thanksgiving break,</p>\r\n<p>Dr. Seals</p>','2011-12-10 15:14:38',0,''),(35,0,23,318,'2011-11-18 21:19:14','STARS Computing Outreach Cary Woods','<p>Hi All,</p>\r\n<p>My AU Stars Fall Outreach was at Cary Woods Elementary School and we performed Lego Robotics.  We work with the Venture Program in our school system which is a program for students who are on are above grade level so that they have time for exploratory ventures as a structured class through the year.  The AUSTARS team spent 6 week this fall and will spend 6 more weeks during Spring 2012 working with Ms. Spencer and her excited class. She chose to pull a small group from her full class and we worked during their Lunch/PE period so that they would not miss their regular instruction. Each student worked with their own robot and the group was 75% female.  A couple of the girls complained that this was too hard and confusing, but everyone completed the program and was very excited and proud of their accomplishment with some parents attending our final day.</p>\r\n<p>Activities that they completed were the following: Building Robots and programming figure challenges, programming maze challenge, etc. (for more details of challenges see <a href=\"http://www.eng.auburn.edu/stars/\" title=\"AUSTARS\">www.eng.auburn.edu/stars/</a> for Projects of computer club.</p>','2011-11-18 21:19:14',0,''),(36,0,57,77,'2011-12-09 19:00:59','UNCC STARS Summer Camp','<p>Check out our plan (work in progress!) for creating a summer camp at UNCC:</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1TgetyJKkztY6EfL6EgZDsIKcYeixuh3sjuXtgfa9bN4/edit\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Summer Camp Google Doc\">https://docs.google.com/document/d/1TgetyJKkztY6EfL6EgZDsIKcYeixuh3sjuXtgfa9bN4/edit</a></p>\r\n<p>Our STARS student organization, entirely student run, has taken the initiative to create the content for the camp.</p>\r\n<p>If you\'d like to get involved with this project, contact<a href=\"mailto:sheggen@uncc.edu\" title=\"Scott Heggen\"> Scott Heggen</a></p>','2012-05-01 20:41:15',0,''),(37,0,58,144,'2011-12-13 22:47:09','Science and Education','<p>What are some science and educational this your doing at your school?</p>','2011-12-14 21:23:14',0,''),(38,0,58,144,'2011-12-14 20:50:19','Recruitment','<p>What types of methods you use for recruitment?</p>','2011-12-14 20:50:19',0,''),(39,0,58,144,'2012-02-03 16:21:14','Mentoring','<p><strong>Find STARS Mentoring Manual by Dr. Nathan Thomas in STARS Public Resources.</strong></p>\r\n<p> </p>','2012-02-03 16:21:14',0,''),(40,0,58,144,'2011-12-14 21:06:23','Articles','<p>Anything that has to do with STARS</p>','2011-12-14 21:06:33',0,''),(41,0,58,144,'2011-12-14 21:09:22','Outreach Activities','<p>Any outreach activities that are done at your school.</p>','2011-12-14 21:09:22',0,''),(42,0,23,318,'2012-01-11 22:43:31','STARS 2012 Intro & Org Meeting','<p>Happy New Year and its time to start getting organized for Spring  STARS 2012.  We hope everyone can return, but if you can\'t please  suggest 1-2 folks that can take your place.  Thanks Dr. Seals</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Use the link below to provide your availability for meeting next week:</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoPlainText\"><a href=\"http://www.doodle.com/ie29xnb66wv8phzn\">http://www.doodle.com/ie29xnb66wv8phzn</a></p>','2012-01-11 22:43:31',0,''),(43,0,11,129,'2012-01-17 20:55:17','What to do at 2012 Celebration?','<p>The 2012 Celebration will be in August.  We should offer some workshops and many of you should present about our outreach efforts.  What things are you interested in presenting on?  What workshops should we offer?  We will have to fly this year.</p>\r\n<p> </p>','2012-01-17 20:55:17',0,''),(94,0,38,185,'2013-01-31 18:42:40','DREU - Questions','<p>Hello,</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">I\'m considering applying for a DREU. Has anyone done this before? Can you offer suggestions? Answer questions?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">Thanks for your help!</span></p>\r\n<p>Margueirte</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>ps: http://cra-w.org/ArticleDetails/tabid/77/ArticleID/54/Distributed-Research-Experiences-for-Undergraduates-DREU.aspx</p>\r\n<p> </p>','2013-01-31 18:42:40',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":0}'),(90,0,66,395,'2013-01-16 15:28:58','Socially Relevant Computing Summer REU at UNC Charlotte','<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;\">The application process for the Socially Relevant Computing Research Experience for Undergraduates at UNC Charlotte is currently open.  Please share the attached flyer with any students you think may be interested in participating in this exciting research opportunity in Charlotte, NC.  The program runs from May 28, 2012 - July 26, 2013.  <strong>Our application deadline is February 24, 2013</strong>.  On-campus housing is available for free and students will receive a participation stipend.  For more information about our program, please visit: <a href=\"http://reu.uncc.edu/\">http://reu.uncc.edu/</a>. </span></p>','2013-01-16 15:28:58',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":1}'),(47,0,58,144,'2012-02-03 16:24:46','Mentoring Models','<p>What type of mentoring model do you use at your school?</p>','2012-02-03 16:24:46',0,''),(48,0,47,122,'2012-02-05 15:06:08','Courseware for Haiti - eToys','<p><span id=\"wall-message-101\">Please use this thread to post eToys resources</span></p>\r\n<p><span>eToys courseware resources<br /><br />Squeakland wiki with courseware<br /><a href=\"http://wiki.squeakland.org/display/sq/Home\" title=\"http://wiki.squeakland.org/display/sq/Home\">http://wiki.squeakland.org/display/sq/Home<br /></a><br />eToys projects made at Illinois<br /><a href=\"http://eToysIllinois.org\" title=\"eToysIllinois.org\">eToysIllinois.org<br /></a><br />eToys projects in many languages<br /><a href=\"http://translate.sugarlabs.org/projects/etoys_new/\" title=\"translate.sugarlabs.org/projects/etoys_new/\">translate.sugarlabs.org/projects/etoys_new/</a></span></p>\r\n','2012-02-05 15:06:08',0,''),(49,0,47,122,'2012-02-06 16:02:53','Books, videos, webpages about Haiti','<p><span id=\"wall-message-102\">Books to read:<br /><br /><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/That-Day-Everybody-Ate-Possibility/dp/0977333892/ref=sr_1_1?s=books&ie=UTF8&qid=1328454533&sr=1-1\">Mountains beyond mountains<br /><br />On that day, everybody ate</a>: <br />A story about an American who went to Haiti and later started a food program<br /><br /><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Haiti-After-Earthquake-Paul-Farmer/dp/1586489739/ref=pd_sim_b_3/190-8690560-8881062\">Haiti after the earthquake</a>:<br />A long discussion of Haiti, Partners for Health, helping after the earthquake<br /><br /><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Travesty-Haiti-Christian-orphanages-trafficking/dp/1419698036/ref=sr_1_1?s=books&ie=UTF8&qid=1328453961&sr=1-1\">Travesty in Haiti</a>:<br />Recommended by Tim<br /><br /><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Creole-Made-Easy-Wally-Turnbull/dp/0967993717/ref=sr_1_1?s=books&ie=UTF8&qid=1328455448&sr=1-1\">Creole made easy</a></span></p>\r\n<p>A video emailed by Osa:</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.ted.com/talks/lang/en/chimamanda_adichie_the_danger_of_a_single_story.html\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: #1155cc; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: normal; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.917969);\">http://www.ted.com/talks/lang/en/chimamanda_adichie_the_danger_of_a_single_story.html</a></p>','2012-02-06 16:02:53',0,''),(50,0,47,167,'2012-02-05 19:54:44','I\'m Going to Haiti and I\'m Bringing...','<p>We are requiring every student (and we\'re asking everyone else) to contribute two items:</p>\r\n<p>1. An eToy or game or something like that, translated to Kreyol (we\'ll help with the translation)</p>\r\n<p>2. A free book (.pdf or .epub) for kids or young adults, in English or French or Kreyol (you won\'t find free ebooks in Kreyol in all likelihood, because Kreyol hasn\'t been a written language for long enough); look on The Internet Archive and/or Protect Gutenberg.</p>\r\n<p>You will be asked to help people learn the toy/game. Language is going to be a problem, so here\'s an idea: try teaching a friend WITHOUT SPEAKING. I have used this as a learning tool for myself and it\'s exceptional (and exceptionally hard).</p>\r\n<p>First come, first served: once you decide on your game and book, post here (WITH A LINK) and it is now reserved for you. Rob Armstrong (rarmst23@uncc.edu) has created a DropBox where you will upload everything, but remember to post here first.</p>','2012-02-05 19:54:44',0,''),(51,0,47,562,'2012-03-05 02:40:27','Book','<p> </p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/When-Night-Falls-Kric-Krac/dp/1563085798/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&qid=1330914218&sr=8-1\">http://www.amazon.com/When-Night-Falls-Kric-Krac/dp/1563085798/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&qid=1330914218&sr=8-1</a></p>\r\n<p>This is a book that I purchased after hearing Tim speak at the training session. Many short stories written by a Haitian woman and translated into English. I have translated 3 of the stories into Haitian Creole using Google translate. I am sure they are not 100% accurate. I will bring the book on the trip.</p>\r\n<p> </p>','2012-03-05 02:40:27',0,''),(52,0,61,118,'2012-03-29 16:10:57','Literature Scan for SSC EA Research Project','<p>Here is the article I found which could really help guide our efforts at SSC with surveying technology event participants.  This has some helpful ideas for our 2013 event surveys:</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;\"> </span><a href=\"http://blog.cvent.com/blog/meeting-and-event-technology-best-practices/make-future-events-better-with-post-event-surveys\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff; font-family: Calibri; font-size: small;\">http://blog.cvent.com/blog/meeting-and-event-technology-best-practices/make-future-events-better-with-post-event-surveys</span></span></a></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;\"> </span></p>\r\n<p> </p>','2012-03-29 16:10:57',0,''),(53,0,60,521,'2012-03-30 19:16:55','Literary Review ','<p>According to its creators, the Lifelong Kindergarten group at the <a class=\"icon_hoovers\" href=\"http://search.proquest.com.prx.library.gatech.edu/pqrl/docview/231156024/135B79D4D3F7A049CFD/2?accountid=11107#\">MIT</a> (Massachusetts Institute of Technology) Media Lab, Scratch is a  \"media-rich programming environment\" that allows first-time programmers  to create animation, games, and other interactive media.  [...] the  Hennepin County Library (HCL; formerly the Minneapolis Public Library)  developed a series of media-rich programming workshops in which students  created projects with Scratch.\\n Also, a summer computer science  program showcasing all three technologies may be attractive to middle  school students.  [...] for elementary school students, an attractive  approach may be a summer reading program that combines storytelling with  PicoCrickets - children can read books and use PicoCricket to create  scenes of their favorite stories.  [...] libraries with busy schedules  can offer these programs once a week, once a month, or as a summer  program of varying lengths.</p>\r\n<p>search.proquest.com.prx.library.gatech.edu/pqrl/docview/231156024/fulltextPDF?accountid=11107</p>','2012-03-30 19:16:55',0,''),(54,0,61,186,'2012-04-02 17:24:32','Literature Scan Paper','<p><strong>Abstract</strong><br /> In this paper, we empirically investigate an extension of the Technology Acceptance Model (TAM) to explain the individual acceptance and usage of websites. Conceptually, we examine perceived ease-of-use, usefulness, enjoyment, and their impact on attitude towards using, intention to use and actual use. The paper also introduces a new construct, \"perceived visual attractiveness\" of the website and demonstrates that it influences usefulness, enjoyment, and ease-of-use. For our empirical research we partnered with a Dutch generic portal site with over 300,000 subscribers at the time the research was conducted. The websurvey resulted in a sample size of 828 respondents. The results confirmed all of the 12 hypotheses formulated.<br /> <br /> <strong>Citation</strong><br /> Hans van der Heijden, Factors influencing the usage of websites: the case of a generic portal in The Netherlands, Information & Management, Volume 40, Issue 6, July 2003, Pages 541-549, ISSN 0378-7206, 10.1016/S0378-7206(02)00079-4. (http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0378720602000794)</p>','2012-04-02 17:24:32',0,''),(55,0,23,318,'2012-04-04 21:56:13','Spring 2012 AU STARS Outreach','<div class=\"discussion-entry\">\r\n<p>Hi AuburnStars, Please share some of your highlight from Spring 2012 outreach activities.</p>\r\n<p>Have a productive week and those members in Boys N Girls Club create your Journal after we complete that activity.</p>\r\n<p>Dr. Seals</p>\r\n</div>','2012-04-24 00:47:22',0,''),(57,0,64,45,'2012-06-12 15:35:14','Issues and bugs','<p>Test post. Or a place to post issues and bugs...</p>\r\n<p>Why didn\'t log in work with Chrome?</p>','2012-09-13 14:32:41',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":\"1\"}'),(58,0,6,139,'2012-07-10 17:50:06','[Started July 10, 2012]  Summer 2012 - Internship or Research?','Students,\r\n\r\nIf you are participating in research this summer, or on an Internship, PLEASE provide the following information by posting to this discussion:\r\n\r\nYour Name:\r\nLocation of your Research/Internship Appointment (company or lab, city and state):\r\nDates of Appointment (From / To):\r\nName of Supervisor:\r\n\r\n\r\nThanks so much!\r\n\r\n- Dr. B','2012-07-15 04:24:00',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":0}'),(59,0,64,45,'2012-07-26 20:32:07','File upload testing','<p>This is a test of uploading files.</p>','2012-07-26 20:32:07',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":\"1\"}'),(60,0,64,294,'2012-07-27 19:17:14','file upload and download','<p>testing</p>','2012-07-27 19:21:53',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":\"1\"}'),(61,0,64,294,'2012-08-02 06:52:17','test discussion','<p>discussion message</p>','2012-08-02 06:52:17',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":\"1\"}'),(62,0,64,294,'2012-08-02 19:46:12','docx','<p>test</p>','2012-08-22 22:13:45',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":\"1\"}'),(63,0,66,45,'2012-08-03 14:43:15','2011-2012 Teleconference minutes','<p>The minutes from the 2011-2012 teleconferences.</p>','2012-08-03 14:43:15',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":\"1\"}'),(64,0,66,45,'2012-08-03 14:46:15','STARS Forms','<p>Various STARS forms will be posted here.</p>','2012-08-03 14:46:15',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":\"1\"}'),(65,0,5,45,'2012-08-03 14:48:00','2011-2012 ESC Teleconference minutes','<p>Minutes posted from the 2011-2012 meetings posted here.</p>','2012-08-03 14:48:00',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":\"1\"}'),(66,0,36,42,'2012-08-03 14:52:31','Mentoring resources','<p>The 2011 Students Mentoring Manual, as well as sets of Mentoring papers.</p>','2012-08-03 14:52:31',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":\"1\"}'),(70,0,65,45,'2012-08-20 18:12:44','Posters for Celebration 2012','<p>Please upload your poster from Celebration here. To make it easier on us, please name your poster p#_Lastname - where # is your poster number.</p>','2012-08-27 18:35:11',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":\"1\"}'),(71,0,65,45,'2012-08-20 18:14:22','Presentations for Celebration 2012','<p>Please upload your presentation from the Celebration here. Please make sure to include the last name of the presenter in the title of the presentation.</p>','2012-09-02 18:00:17',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":\"1\"}'),(74,0,65,73,'2012-08-27 20:28:12','Vote for STARS at the 2013 SXSW Conference!','<p>Want to see STARS represented at the 2013 SXSW Conference? Help us get on the agenda by voting for our panel! Sessions only make the program by number of votes, so we really need you to vote for our session and forward to all friends you know, share on facebook, twitter and linked-in and get everyone to vote!<br /><br />South by Southwest is the largest interactive conference in the US bringing together creative minds, scientific minds and innovative minds in one place. So please vote and get the word out. VOTES MUST BE CAST BY AUGUST 31!!!  More details on SXSW and the panel picker below. You must log-in to vote!<br /><br />More Women Creating Technology Innovations (Bring Gender Diversity in Technology to SXSW): http://panelpicker.sxsw.com/vote/5688</p>','2012-08-27 20:28:12',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":0}'),(75,0,8,545,'2012-09-12 18:40:27','September Monthly Meeting','<p>Please be aware that the next scheduled monthly meeting will be on October 6, 2012 at noon. Please check your emails for upcoming minutes from last meeting and agenda for next meeting. If there are any itmems you would like to have on the agenda please let me or Professor Brauda know in advance.</p>','2012-09-19 16:07:00',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":\"1\"}'),(77,0,71,560,'2012-09-24 17:47:49','How can we increase the awareness, knowledge, and interest of high school girls in IT? ','<p>We plan to discuss career opportunities when presenting at Salisbury High School.  What other topics might be beneficial? </p>','2012-10-29 14:46:08',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":0}'),(78,0,40,395,'2012-09-26 20:11:13','2012-2013 Teleconference Minutes','<p>This is where minutes from the monthly teleconference will be can be found.  If you are unable to make a meeting, be sure to check here for the minutes!</p>','2012-09-26 20:11:13',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":\"1\"}'),(79,0,5,395,'2012-10-12 19:29:01','2012-2013 Teleconference Minutes','<p>Find the minutes for the 2012-2013 ESC teleconferences here!</p>','2012-10-12 19:29:01',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":\"1\"}'),(82,0,65,649,'2012-10-25 22:40:06','Gamemaker use - 30 day licensure','<p>We are a new STARS institution and heard a lot about the use of Gamemaker for an outreach activity. When we looked into this is appears there is a 30-day free license. Did other institutions encounter this and do you have recommendations/suggestions on how to work with this characteristic?</p>','2012-10-29 19:18:57',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":\"1\"}'),(158,0,100,925,'2014-03-28 18:12:49','Who are we?','<p>Get to know others in your group. Post information about yourself.</p>','2014-03-28 18:12:49',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":0}'),(159,0,100,925,'2014-03-28 18:12:12','What is your favorite blog?','<p>Talk about what blog is your favorite and why?</p>','2014-03-28 18:12:12',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":0}'),(160,0,100,925,'2014-03-28 18:13:56','Why did you join this group?','<p>Explain why you joined this group.</p>','2014-03-28 18:13:56',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":0}'),(84,0,21,790,'2012-11-05 14:32:37','Publicity?....','<p>Hey all, I was wondering if you all will be interested in doing a joint operation with the Eucledians Club.To host a video-game tournament in order to get more students involved with what we do and how we can help them for coming to the event. It will be more of a meet and greet type of program. Where we win them over with games and inform them on what we actually do and how we help out in the community. I think it will great to do so. Any ideas comments or concerns, or even a better way to improve my idea feel free to let me know.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks in advance, Luis Figueroa</p>','2012-11-05 14:32:37',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":\"1\"}'),(85,0,66,45,'2012-11-05 17:14:55','2012-2013 Teleconference minutes','<p>See the minutes in this discussion, as well as any comments about the meetings</p>','2012-11-05 17:14:55',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":\"1\"}'),(86,0,65,745,'2012-11-14 17:14:56','STARS Narrative upload','<p>This is for uploading narrative files for 2012.</p>','2012-11-18 21:00:06',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":\"1\"}'),(87,0,20,862,'2012-11-16 20:44:35','Galaga Project','<p>Ideas/Comments on our current project.</p>','2012-12-10 19:23:07',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":\"1\"}'),(156,0,5,395,'2014-02-04 15:26:00','2013-2014 Teleconference Minutes','<p>Please find the minutes for teleconferences during the 2013-2014 year here.</p>','2014-02-04 15:26:00',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":1}'),(157,0,100,925,'2014-03-28 18:07:35','What is the best blogging site?','<p>Talk about what the best blogging site is and why?</p>','2014-03-28 18:07:35',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":0}'),(89,0,28,949,'2013-01-10 22:02:01','Hello new person here','<p>I had a nicely prepared post but the interwebs had a divide by zero error and ate it.  >_<</p>\r\n<p>Anyway,  my name\'s Angela Gonzales. I go by \"Ang\" (pronounced as the first  syllable to \'Angela\'). I am in the BS-IT Program and was encouraged to  join (in a *very* enthusiastic manner) this group so I hope that I will  be a help to this group and get to know everyone here.</p>\r\n<p>Typically I  take on-campus courses since I find that\'s the best way that I learn  but the way things have turned out for this term, everything\'s going to  be online. So this means that I <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">need</span> to stay up to date with events so that I know when to plan a <em>visit</em> to campus (I live in the UCF area and it\'s almost a 40 min. commute to the SLM campus).</p>\r\n<p>At  home, I provide medical assistance for two family members so I must  manage my time wisely. (most of the homework I do is while waiting in a  Dr.\'s waiting room) For hobbies, I enjoy games (video, tabletop),  LOLcats, drawing, programming, and poking at electronics with a stick  (i.e. experiment with stuff) which is how to create/run a minecraft  server right at the moment.</p>\r\n<p>Anyway, I hope that this brief \'hello\'  should be enough to start with and I hope that it doesn\'t get eaten  again. (Um, would that count as a valid excuse for why someone\'s  homework is turned in late?)</p>\r\n<p>P.S. This thing went \"Derp\" again - session timed out. (yay for notepad!)</p>','2013-01-10 22:02:01',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":1}'),(92,0,79,73,'2013-01-28 15:22:03','Documents for 1.28.13 call','<p>See attached documents for discussion on today\'s call:</p>\r\n<p>Celebration Project Plan</p>\r\n<p>Celebration Rolls and Tasks</p>\r\n<p>Proposed deadlines</p>','2013-01-28 19:41:08',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":1}'),(93,0,80,185,'2013-01-28 16:53:00','Artifacts from our user','<p>I am uploading the artifacts our users have sent us.</p>','2013-01-31 17:17:20',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":0}'),(155,0,64,45,'2014-01-24 21:50:28','Anyone get this email??','<p>Just checking on the email status... Not sure emails are going out properly.</p>','2014-01-24 21:50:28',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":0}'),(154,0,66,395,'2013-11-08 12:37:40','2013-2014 Teleconference Minutes','<p>Here you will find the minutes for AL teleconference meetings this academic year.</p>\r\n<p> </p>','2013-11-08 12:37:40',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":1}'),(98,0,83,321,'2013-02-05 13:59:22','Goals for Spring 2013','<p><span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>As a team, the Robotics group has a major goal for Spring 2013 in that it wants to have a successful Middle School outreach trip. We plan to complete a maze game that children can participate in and solve problems using Teleop functionality with the robots and simple computing and logic skills they will learn throughout the game.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>By focusing on Middle school as an age range, this allows us time to focus on the hardware and teleop functionality of the Create-ASUS robots. As a team, we do not have the best grasp on the coding aspects of the shorthand language used for a robots. However, we are getting a definite hang of the hardware limitations of the robots.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span>We definitely have room for more members this semester and will be meeting Thursdays at 4:00 p.m. in the Thurmond Linux Lab.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>-Jesse</p>','2013-02-05 13:59:22',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":0}'),(151,0,64,42,'2013-08-22 17:55:34','Additional discussion Test','<p>Hi</p>','2013-08-22 17:56:55',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":0}'),(152,0,66,395,'2013-09-03 17:47:34','ARTSI Robotics Competition/Tapia','<p class=\"MsoPlainText\">We hope that you enjoyed the workshop at the STARS Celebration on preparing for the 2014 ARTSI Robotics Competition, which will be held at the Tapia Celebration of Diversity in Computing in February 2014. If you are thinking of participating in the robotics competition, we encourage you to apply for a Tapia travel scholarship! Travel scholarships are available for both faculty and students. The application process for Tapia travel scholarships is separate from registering for the ARTSI Robotics Competition. To apply for a Tapia travel scholarship, submit your application at <a href=\"http://tapiaconference.org/participate/scholarships\">http://tapiaconference.org/participate/scholarships</a>. Make sure to mention that you are planning to participate in the ARTSI Robotics Competition in your application. The deadline for Tapia travel scholarship applications is September 12, 2013.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoPlainText\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">For more information about the ARTSI Robotics Competition, see </span><a href=\"http://www.cs.cmu.edu/~dst/ARTSI/Robotics14/\" style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">http://www.cs.cmu.edu/~dst/ARTSI/Robotics14/</a><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">. </span></p>','2013-09-03 17:47:34',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":0}'),(100,0,6,139,'2013-02-05 21:10:21','Update on the STARS SCC Committees for 2013','<p>Students,<br /><br />We are revising our committees with STARS, so that we  can better streamline what we are doing and make sure that activities do  not overlap.  As a result, we have narrowed the committees to the  following:<br /><br />Mentoring - strictly within the department.  Chairs  will work with committee to plan mentoring events (such as pairing  mentors with mentees, holding social events, etc.)<br /><br />Recruitment:   strictly with K-12 schools; Chairs will work with committee to plan  events designed to interest kids in computing as a career (such as  events at high schools, Career Days, hosting high schools on campus,  etc)<br /><br />Academic and Outreach: again with K-12 but can be otherwise;  Committee will work SOLELY on workshops and learning events (i.e.,  workshops on gaming, hack-a-thons, learning events like a computer crime  workshop for the community)<br /><br />Leadership and Professional  Development: solely for FAMU students;  committee will plan seminars on  various topics, as well as work with companies if necessary.<br /><br />Important Points:<br />- I would like each committee to have a chair and co-chair<br />- ALL members of STARS MUST belong to AT LEAST ONE committee<br /><br />Your Job:<br />-  You must email me your committee choices by Friday, Feb. 8; you must  also indicate if you wish to be a chair or co-chair of the committee at  that time</p>','2013-02-05 21:10:21',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":0}'),(101,0,84,488,'2013-02-10 04:49:30','Morehouse STARS Racks Up Awards','<p>And other photos from the conference....</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p> </p>','2013-02-10 04:49:30',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":0}'),(102,0,64,45,'2013-02-22 13:21:45','Testing the email','<p>Blah blah blah</p>','2013-02-22 13:21:45',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":0}'),(103,0,64,925,'2013-02-22 21:15:19','Test SES','<p>working?</p>','2013-02-22 21:32:17',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":0}'),(104,0,66,45,'2013-02-22 21:35:37','Email issue for the online community','<p>We recently discovered some of the emails from the online community were not getting delivered, and finally found an hourly email limit on our host that we were not made aware of was sometimes being exceeded. We have moved email hosts, which has resolved most problems and we are now hunting down some remaining bugs in how this software sends email and will hopefully have this all fixed by Monday.</p>\r\n<p>So, if a student says they didn\'t receive an email about a discussion or event you posted recently, they may be correct. Everything is correct once you log in, its just the emails that were impacted. If you spot any more issues or have any questions, add to this discussion and let me know! I apologize for any inconvenience.</p>','2013-02-22 21:35:37',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":0}'),(105,0,79,73,'2013-02-25 15:31:03','Documents for 2.25.13 Call','<p>I\'ve uploaded the recent project plan for the call today. Minutes and other attachments will be uploaded after the call.</p>','2013-02-26 15:35:05',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":0}'),(109,0,34,185,'2013-02-26 19:05:12','Spring 2013 - Mid semester checkup','<p>I would like to hear from all project leaders. Please spend just a few minutes to get me up to speed on your activities.</p>\r\n<p><br /><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\"> How are things going?</span></p>\r\n<p>- What have you accomplished so far this semester?</p>\r\n<p>- What are your plans for the rest of the semester?  You should be specific about what you want to do this semester.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Community building?</p>\r\n<p>- How have you used our new bulletin board to help promote your activities?</p>\r\n<p>- How have you used the Stars Online website?</p>\r\n<p>- What are some plans to build up your project and keep it growing?</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Thanks,<br />Dr. Doman</p>\r\n<p> </p>','2013-02-26 19:05:12',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":1}'),(107,0,65,73,'2013-02-25 21:57:57','STARS Celebration Shirts and Business Cards - Love them or Hate them?','<p>A recent discussion came up about the STARS shirts and business cards provided at Celebration and we need your input. Do you find these items useful and beneficial? If so, let us know - if not, tell us why and how we can modify, update, eliminate or make them so. We want your ideas to help us shape Celebration for this year!</p>','2013-03-25 15:35:40',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":0}'),(110,0,34,185,'2013-02-26 19:05:27','Spring 2013 - Mid semester checkup','<p>I would like to hear from all project leaders. Please spend just a few minutes to get me up to speed on your activities.</p>\r\n<p><br /><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\"> How are things going?</span></p>\r\n<p>- What have you accomplished so far this semester?</p>\r\n<p>- What are your plans for the rest of the semester?  You should be specific about what you want to do this semester.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Community building?</p>\r\n<p>- How have you used our new bulletin board to help promote your activities?</p>\r\n<p>- How have you used the Stars Online website?</p>\r\n<p>- What are some plans to build up your project and keep it growing?</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Thanks,<br />Dr. Doman</p>\r\n<p> </p>','2013-03-17 19:18:11',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":1}'),(111,0,66,185,'2013-02-26 20:06:56','Position available, Winthrop Computer Science Dept','<p>FYI.</p>','2013-02-26 20:12:07',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":1}'),(112,0,65,73,'2013-02-28 16:39:28','STARS Celebration 2013 Call For Participation Open!','<h2>Empowering 21st Century Tech Leaders!</h2>\r\n<p>Call for Participation is <strong>Now Open through April 28, 2013</strong>! Visit the Celebration website to access the submission site and review the session tracks, guidelines and dates!</p>\r\n<p>http://starscelebration.org/stars-celebration-cfp</p>\r\n<p>The STARS Celebration seeks to promote inspiration, creativity and  innovation in its participants as well as a sense of community. This  year\'s them of <em>empowerment </em>aims to develop and share the  talents we have within. Join us for an exciting and informative blend of  cutting-edge sessions, shared experiences, and camaraderie with other  computing students and professionals.</p>\r\n<p>We invite all computing researchers, faculty, staff, partners, and  students to contribute panels, presentations, workshops, lightening  talks, birds-of-a-feather, or posters.</p>\r\n<p>See you in Atlanta!</p>','2013-02-28 16:39:28',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":0}'),(113,0,81,185,'2013-03-18 20:35:34','Karissa Martindale Speaking Date','<p>Please check out the event on Karissa Martindale.  If you can come, update the event</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>I\'d like to see how this online community works.</p>','2013-03-18 20:35:34',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":0}'),(114,0,66,104,'2013-03-21 14:03:27','SLC Alumni Update','<p>It\'s that time of year again- SLC Alumni updates. Attached is a comprehensive spreadsheet of every SLC student to date. Please provide updates on your student whereabouts in the NOTES column by <strong>April 5</strong>. Summary:</p>\r\n<p>1. fill in graduation dates and degrees obtained by your former SLC students in the indicated columns</p>\r\n<p>2. this list contains what we have on record from your past submissions of this information</p>\r\n<p>3. return the completed list for your school without altering the spreadsheet format by email to audrey.rorrer@uncc.edu</p>\r\n<p><strong>This is due by April 5th. </strong> We rely on these updates to compile retention data for the STARS Alliance.</p>\r\n<p>We have a corresponding SLC Student Alumni Survey that has been sent to past participants; unfortunately, many of the email addresses we have on file are school addresses, so your input is critical.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Thank you!</p>\r\n<p> </p>','2013-03-21 14:03:27',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":1}'),(115,0,79,73,'2013-03-22 15:53:21','Documents for 3.25.13 Call','<p>Documents for the call on 3.25 will be added to this discussion. Thanks!</p>','2013-03-22 15:53:21',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":0}'),(116,0,65,73,'2013-04-01 15:57:10','STARS Celebration 2013 - Call For Participation Deadline April 12!','<p>The deadline is quickly approaching to submit your posters, presentations, panels, workshops, lightning talks or BoF for this year\'s STARS Celebration. Sumbissions are due <strong>by midnight April 12. </strong>Everyone is encouraged to submit a topic! If you have industry or academic contacts that you think would also add to this year\'s conference theme, Empowering 21st Century Tech Leaders, encourage them to submit as well!</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Visit the submission page <a href=\"http://www.starscelebration.org/stars-celebration-cfp\" target=\"_blank\">here!</a> We look froward to seeing you in August!</p>','2013-04-14 02:26:47',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":0}'),(117,0,65,134,'2013-04-09 14:29:57','CS UNPLUGGED','<p>Our group is trying to start a CS Unplugged relationship with a local  Elementary School. Can anyone share insights with me on which activities  are most effective and fun for 5th grade students? <br /><br />Or any other helpful hints you may have from experience when working with 5th graders or CS Unplugged in general?<br /><br />THANK YOU!!!</p>','2013-04-09 14:29:57',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":1}'),(125,0,64,45,'2013-04-09 16:28:56','Creating multiple','<p>blahb lahb lah</p>','2013-08-05 16:49:44',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":0}'),(126,0,65,73,'2013-04-15 16:53:47','STARS Celebration 2013 - Call For Participation Deadline Extended to April 19','<p>The submission deadline for STARS Celebration 2013 has been extended to <strong>Friday, April 19</strong>. We received several emails indicating access the submission site was unavailable. Please note the instructions below for submitting your proposal.</p>\r\n<p>Posters, panels, presentations, lighting talks and BOF are still needed for this year\'s conference. Be sure and submit your best practices and activities to share with your peers.</p>\r\n<p>If you are still experiencing difficulty, please contact <strong>Ashley Peeler @ ashley.peeler@uncc.edu</strong> or <strong>Scott Heggen @ sheggen@uncc.edu</strong></p>\r\n<p>1. Visit <a href=\"http://www.starscelebration.org\" target=\"_blank\">www.starscelebration.org</a></p>\r\n<p>2. Click on the menu tab that reads \"<a href=\"http://starscelebration.org/stars-celebration-cfp\" target=\"_blank\">Call for Participation</a>\" - here you will find all relevant submission topic information</p>\r\n<p>3. Click on the menu tab that reads \"<a href=\"http://starscelebration.org/stars-celebration-submission-instructions\" target=\"_blank\">Submission Instructions</a>\" - here you will find the requirements and instructions on creating an EasyChair account and how to submit.</p>\r\n<p>4. If this does not work, you can follow this link to sign in or create an account. <a href=\"https://www.easychair.org/account/signin.cgi?conf=starscelebration2013\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.easychair.org/account/signin.cgi?conf=starscelebration2013</a></p>\r\n<p>Thank you from your 2013 Celebration Program Committee</p>','2013-04-15 16:53:47',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":0}'),(119,0,65,134,'2013-04-09 14:36:28','CS UNPLUGGED','<p>Our group is trying to start a CS Unplugged relationship with a local  Elementary School. Can anyone share insights with me on which activities  are most effective and fun for 5th grade students? <br /><br />Or any other helpful hints you may have from experience when working with 5th graders or CS Unplugged in general?<br /><br />THANK YOU!!!</p>','2013-04-17 19:25:31',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":1}'),(121,0,64,45,'2013-04-09 16:25:07','blah','<p>testing</p>','2013-04-09 16:25:07',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":1}'),(122,0,64,45,'2013-04-09 16:28:50','Creating multiple','<p>blahb lahb lah</p>','2013-04-09 16:28:50',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":0}'),(123,0,64,45,'2013-04-09 16:28:52','Creating multiple','<p>blahb lahb lah</p>','2013-04-09 16:28:52',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":0}'),(124,0,64,45,'2013-04-09 16:28:54','Creating multiple','<p>blahb lahb lah</p>','2013-04-09 16:28:54',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":0}'),(127,0,65,73,'2013-04-19 20:51:52','CFP Deadline Reminder = TONIGHT!','<p>Last call for proposal submissions for Celebration is tonight. Be sure and submit your ideas! All are welcome and encouraged!! If you have trouble contact Ashley at ashley.peeler@uncc.edu or Scott at sheggen@uncc.edu</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Visit <a href=\"http://www.starscelebration.org\" target=\"_blank\">www.starscelebration.org</a> for more information!</p>\r\n<p>Happy proposing!</p>','2013-04-19 20:51:52',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":0}'),(128,0,79,73,'2013-04-22 14:38:40','Documents for 4.22.13 Call','<p>Hi all, please find attached documents for the 4.22 call. We will continue to upload items here rather than sending emails. Today\'s focus will be on the program.</p>\r\n<p> </p>','2013-04-22 14:38:40',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":0}'),(129,0,23,318,'2013-04-22 17:19:29','Spring  Outreach Journals','<p>Journal Outreach Template: <br />What did you enjoy most about the Alice Outreach program? (This program exposed students to Alice through introductory visual programming and they created animated stories or games.)<br /><br />Which do you think our participants enjoyed the most?<br /><br />What did you enjoy least about the Alice program?<br /><br />Would you like to work with Alice or a similar program in the future? <br />Please check one choice.     ___YES      	___NO<br />Please make suggestions to improve the program.<br /><br />Please suggest a friend or someone that you tutored that would be suitable for tutoring mentor next summer or next fall.</p>','2013-04-22 17:19:29',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":1}'),(130,0,23,318,'2013-04-22 17:20:44','Journal Tutoring Template','<p>What did you enjoy most about peer mentoring through CSSE STARS tutoring? What was the most rewarding aspect? (This program worked with students to improve their Java programming and programmed debugging/problem solving.)<br /><br />Which do you think was most rewarding for the participants?<br /><br />What was the least rewarding aspect of tutoring? If this relates to a program feature, Please suggest an improvement to this feature of the program.<br /><br />Would you like to work with the tutoring program in the future? <br />Please check one choice.     ___YES       ___NO<br /><br />Please make suggestions to improve the program.<br /><br />Please suggest a friend or someone that you tutored that would be suitable for tutoring mentor next summer or next fall.</p>','2013-04-22 17:20:44',0,'{\"filepermission-member\":1}'),(131,0,65,73,'2013-05-15 19:03:02','STARS Award Nominations - now being accepted!','<p>Nominations are now being accepted for the <strong>2013 STARS Awards</strong>, to be presented at the final night of the 2013 Celebration in August. Nominations will be accepted in the following categories:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Outstanding Evaluation Assistant</li>\r\n<li>Outstanding Corps Award (institution)</li>\r\n<li>Outstanding Corps Student (individual)</li>\r\n<li>Outstanding Faculty/Liaison </li>\r\n<li>Outstanding Community Partner</li>\r\n<li>Outstanding Industry Partner</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>  Normal 0     false false false  EN-US X-NONE X-NONE              MicrosoftInternetExplorer4              </p>\r\n                                                                                                                                            \r\n\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:\"Table Normal\";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowban